kind: llman.sdd.spec
name: "cli-entry"
purpose: "TBD - created by archiving change c110-update-slash-commands. Update purpose after archive."
valid_scope[2]: src/,tests/
requirements[14]{req_id,title,statement}:
  sc1,"info-fields",SlashCommandInfo MUST carry name description source and source_info fields.
  sc2,"source-enum",SlashCommandSource MUST be exactly one of extension prompt or skill.
  sc3,"builtin-table",System MUST provide the full builtin slash command table matching pi semantics including export compact tree fork and reload.
  sc4,dispatch,AgentSession MUST dispatch slash commands via dispatch_slash_command routing to the matching handler.
  rpc1,"stdio-transport",System MUST provide an RPC mode that reads JSONL commands from stdin and writes JSONL events to stdout.
  rpc2,"command-coverage",RpcCommand MUST cover prompt steer follow_up abort new_session get_state set_model cycle_model get_available_models set_thinking_level cycle_thinking_level set_steering_mode set_follow_up_mode compact set_auto_compaction set_auto_retry abort_retry bash abort_bash get_session_stats export_html switch_session fork clone get_fork_messages get_last_assistant_text set_session_name get_messages and get_commands.
  rpc3,"event-streaming",RPC mode MUST subscribe to the AgentEvent stream and emit corresponding RpcEvent lines on stdout.
  rpc4,"signal-shutdown",RPC mode MUST handle SIGINT and SIGTERM with graceful abort and clean process exit.
  rpc5,"id-correlation",Each RPC command and its response MUST carry an optional id field for request correlation.
  ce1,"interactive-directory","The CLI and print modules MUST live under src/interactive/cli/ and src/interactive/print/; the directory MUST NOT be named interface/; interactive/ modules MUST depend only on agent::facade and protocol/, never on agent::runtime, agent::session, or agent::tools directly."
  ce2,"no-silent-fallback","When a config file is present but yields zero loadable models (e.g. wrong key like 'model:' instead of 'models:'), the CLI MUST emit a clear error pointing at the config instead of silently falling back to environment-variable defaults. Silent fall-through to placeholder defaults is forbidden."
  ce6,"driver-abstraction","System MUST provide an interactive::Driver trait that interactive/cli (and future tui/web) depend on; an InProcessDriver (composition root wiring agent ports) and a RemoteDriver (WebSocket+REST client) MUST both implement it; switching local vs remote MUST require changing only the Driver constructor, not the event-handling code."
  ce7,"composition-root-ports","The in-process composition root (interactive::cli) MUST construct Arc<dyn SessionStore> and Arc<dyn EventSink> from concrete infra types and pass them to facade::Agent::new; the RPC run entry MUST also accept the store and sink for constructing Agent."
  ce8,"server-subcommands","The CLI MUST provide subcommands under server: run (start the server process with optional --port), install (register as launchd/systemd service), and stop (signal the running server via SIGTERM to its PID from the lock file)."
scenarios[16]{req_id,id,given,when,then}:
  sc1,fields,a command originates from a skill,the command is queried,source is skill and source_info is set
  sc2,"source-values",command sources are enumerated,the set is inspected,values are extension prompt or skill only
  sc3,"builtin-table",builtin commands are listed,the table is inspected,it includes export compact tree fork and reload
  sc4,"dispatch-compact",user types compact in a session,dispatch_slash_command is invoked,the compaction handler runs
  sc4,"dispatch-export",user types export in a session,dispatch_slash_command is invoked,the export handler runs
  rpc1,roundtrip,rpc mode is started,a prompt command is sent on stdin,response lines are emitted on stdout
  rpc2,"model-cycle",a cycle_model command is sent,the handler runs,the state response reflects the new model
  rpc2,bash,a bash command is sent,the handler runs,a bash result event is emitted
  rpc3,events,the agent streams text deltas,TextDelta events occur,jsonl event lines are emitted on stdout
  rpc4,sigint,a long running prompt is active,SIGINT is received,an abort is emitted and the process exits cleanly
  rpc5,id,a command with id 42 is sent,the response is produced,the response carries id 42
  ce1,"cli-under-interactive",the source tree is inspected,src/interactive/cli exists and src/interface does not,the rename and dependency isolation are complete
  ce2,"typo-error","","config.yaml is present but its models map is empty due to a typo (model: vs models:)",the CLI errors out with a message referencing the config file rather than silently using a placeholder default
  ce6,"same-handler-both-drivers",an interactive client event handler is written once,it is run against InProcessDriver then RemoteDriver,both produce identical event sequences for the same input
  ce7,"cli-constructs-ports","interactive::cli::run is traced",the agent construction is inspected,"Agent::new receives Arc<dyn SessionStore> and Arc<dyn EventSink>"
  ce8,"server-stop-signals",a server is running with a lock file containing PID 12345,xylitol server stop is run,SIGTERM is sent to PID 12345 and the lock file is cleaned up
